Title: Carbon Dioxide Absorption (Near to Mid IR)
Carbon Dioxide Absorption (Mid to Far IR)
Earth Transmission
How: A telescope-mounted spectrometer on Earth captured sunlight that passed (i.e. transmitted) through Earth’s atmosphere and was reflected off the Moon’s surface back to Earth.
Credit: Pallé, E., Osorio, M. R. Z., Barrena, R., Montañés-Rodríguez, P., & Martín, E. L. (2009). Earth’s transmission spectrum from lunar eclipse observations. Nature, 459(7248), 814-816.
Additional Info: See “Supplementary Information” section of paper cited above for a diagram that shows how the spectrum was obtained.

Title: Clear Hot Jupiter Model Transmission
How: Computer generated based on scientific assumptions about composition of this type of planetary atmosphere
Credit: Sing, D. K., Fortney, J. J., Nikolov, N., Wakeford, H. R., Kataria, T., Evans, T. M., ... & Wilson, P. A. (2016). A continuum from clear to cloudy hot-Jupiter exoplanets without primordial water depletion. Nature, 529(7584), 59-62.
